def: An order of ganoid fishes, including the modern gar pikes andmany allied fossil forms. They have rhombic, ganoid scales, aheterocercal tail, paired fins without an axis, fulcra on the fins,and a bony skeleton, with the vertebr√¶ convex in front and concavebehind, forming a ball and socket joint. See Ganoidel.
A clay ironstone found in Ceylon.
A genus of raptorial birds, including the European kite.
Made of bran; furfuraceous. [R.] "Furfurous bread." SydneySmith.
To provide beforehand. "The materials preprovided." Fuller.
Absence or defect of symmetry; asymmetry.
Unsteady; dizzy; tottery. [Obs.or Prov. Eng.] Sir W. Scott.For yet his noule [head] was totty of the must. Spenser.
Circular motion in a direction contrary to some other circularmotion.
